Zest and halve the @lemon{1}. In a #mixing bowl{}, combine half the @dried oregano{1}(divided), half the @mild paprika{1}(divided), the lemon zest, half the lemon juice, a drizzle of @oil{} and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Add the @chicken thigh{390%g}(diced) to the bowl and stir well to coat. Pop two portions of the chicken onto a #baking tray{} and leave the rest in the bowl.

> IMPORTANT: Remember to wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat!

Halve and peel the @onion{1}(peeled and halved). Chop into wedges. Halve the @bell pepper{1}(halved and seeded) and discard the cores and seeds. Slice into thin strips. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Chop the @chives{1}(chopped). Pop two portions of the @green pepper{1}(halved and seeded) and onion onto the tray with the chicken. Season and drizzle with oil. Set aside.

Heat a glug of oil in a large #ovenproof saucepan{} on medium-high heat. Add the reserved chicken (from the bowl) and cook, turning, until browned, ~{5-6%minutes}. Add the remaining onion and peppers. Fry until soft, ~{5%minutes}. Stir in the garlic and remaining oregano and paprika then add the @chopped tomatoes{1/2%cup}, a pinch of @sugar{pinch}, the @chicken stock powder{1/2%tbsp} and @water{200%ml}.

> TIP: If you don't have an ovenproof pan, just use a saucepan and transfer to an ovenproof dish before putting in the oven.

Bring to the boil, then mix in the @orzo{180%g} and chives. Season with salt and pepper. Transfer to the middle shelf of your #oven{}, uncovered, and bake until almost all the liquid has been absorbed, ~{15%minutes}. At the same time, pop the tray of chicken and veggies on the top shelf for ~{10-15%minutes}. Meanwhile, grate the @mature cheddar cheese{30%g}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

Slice lengthways into the @avocado{1}. Once you reach the stone turn the avocado around to cut in half. Twist each half and pull apart. Remove the stone then scoop the insides onto a board. Slice into thin strips.

Once the orzo is done, stir in the @baby spinach{62.5%g} (leaving a handful back for lunch!). Sprinkle over half the cheddar (the rest will go in your wraps!). Return to the oven to melt, ~{5%minutes}. Serve in bowls and enjoy!

Once you have finished eating, return to your wraps. Lay your @super soft tortillas with whole wheat{4} (2 per person) on a #board{}. Divide up the remaining spinach, roasted veggies, chicken pieces, cheddar and avocado strips, layering them into the centre of each wrap. Squeeze over some lemon juice and add the remainder chives. Fold the two short ends in, over the top of the filling then roll up! Pop into a #box{} and refrigerate. Enjoy Tomorrow!